The paper discusses wireless channel models and their statistical properties, which are relevant for the characterization of the lower tail of the Cumulative Distribution Function (CDF). This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI), as well as system and control theory (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
